class=\"FoldBox_title___fdpp\">词根词缀</h3><div class=\"FoldBox_content__HsTfE\"><div class=\"Affix_affix__iiL_9\"><p>词根<!-- -->: <!-- -->ver</p><p>=true,表示&quot;真实&quot;</p><ul><li><h4>adj.</h4><div><h5>veracious<!-- --> <!-- -->诚实的,说真话的</h5><p>ver真实+acious多……的→很多真实→可靠的</p></div><div><h5>verifiable<!-- --> <!-- -->能作证的, 能证实的</h5><p>verify[v.证实,查证;证明]+able能……的→verifiable能作证的</p></div><div><h5>verisimilar<!-- --> <!-- -->好象真实的</h5><p>veri=ver真实+similar一样→和真的一样</p></div><div><h5>very<!-- --> <!-- -->真正的, 真实的, 恰好的</h5><p>ver真实+y→真正的, 真实的→完全</p></div></li><li><h4>adv.</h4><div><h5>very<!-- --> <!-- -->很,甚,及其,非常,完全 </h5><p>ver真实+y→真正的, 真实的→完全</p></div></li><li><h4>n.</h4><div><h5>veracity<!-- --> <!-- -->真实性,诚实</h5><p>ver真实+acity特性→n.真实性,诚实</p></div><div><h5>verdict<!-- --> <!-- -->[陪审团的]裁决,判决;判断;定论</h5><p>ver真实+dict说→说真话</p></div><div><h5>verity<!-- --> <!-- -->真实, 事实, 真理, 真实的陈述</h5><p>ver真实+ity表名词→n.真实, 事实, 真理, 真实的陈述</p></div></li><li><h4>v.</h4><div><h5>verify<!-- --> <!-- -->证实,查证;证明</h5><p>ver真实+ify表动词→使真实</p></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"Affix_affix__iiL_9\"><p>后缀<!-- -->: <!-- -->-acity</p><p>表名词,&quot;有……倾向;能力或特性等&quot;</p><ul><li><h4>n.</h4><div><h5>capacity<!-- --> <!-- -->容量,才能</h5><p>cap拿,抓+acity有……倾向;能力或特性等→拿住的能力→容量;才能</p></div><div><h5>audacity<!-- --> <!-- -->大胆,鲁莽</h5><p>auda大胆+acity有……倾向;能力或特性等→n.大胆,鲁莽</p></div><div><h5>loquacity<!-- --> <!-- -->多话,饶舌</h5><p>loqu说话+acity有……倾向;能力或特性等→n.多话,饶舌</p></div><div><h5>mendacity<!-- --> <!-- -->虚假</h5><p>mend缺点+acity有……倾向;能力或特性等→n.虚假</p></div><div><h5>rapacity<!-- --> <!-- -->掠夺,贪婪</h5><p>rap夺+acity有……倾向;能力或特性等→n.掠夺,贪婪</p></div><div><h5>tenacity<!-- --> <!-- -->坚持,固执</h5><p>ten握住+acity有……倾向;能力或特性等→tenacious的名词</p></div><div><h5>veracity<!-- --> <!-- -->真实性,诚实</h5><p>ver真+acity有……倾向;能力或特性等→n.真实性,诚实</p></div></li></ul></div></div></div></li><li><div class=\"FoldBox_fold__j7cgz\"><h3 class=\"FoldBox_title___fdpp\">同义词</h3><div class=\"FoldBox_fold__j7cgz\"><h3 class=\"FoldBox_title___fdpp\">英英释义</h3><div class=\"FoldBox_content__HsTfE\"><div class=\"EngMean_eng__Q0uG8\"><h4>Noun</h4><ul><li><h5>1. money extracted as a penalty</h5></li></ul></div><div class=\"EngMean_eng__Q0uG8\"><h4>Verb</h4><ul><li><h5>1. issue a ticket or a fine to as a penalty;</h5><p>\"I was fined for parking on the wrong side of the street\"</p><p>\"Move your car or else you will be ticketed!\"</p></li></ul></div><div class=\"EngMean_eng__Q0uG8\"><h4>Adjective</h4><ul><li><h5>1. superior to the average;</h5><p>\"in <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> spirits\"</p><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> student\"</p><p>\"made good grades\"</p><p>\"morale was good\"</p><p>\"had good weather for the parade\"</p></li><li><h5>2. being satisfactory or in satisfactory condition;</h5><p>\"an all-right movie\"</p><p>\"the passengers were shaken up but are all right\"</p><p>\"is everything all right?\"</p><p>\"everything's <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b>\"</p><p>\"things are okay\"</p><p>\"dinner and the movies had been <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b>\"</p><p>\"another minute I'd have been <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b>\"</p></li><li><h5>3. minutely precise especially in differences in meaning;</h5><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> distinction\"</p></li><li><h5>4. of texture; being small-grained or smooth to the touch or having fine particles;</h5><p>\"wood with a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> grain\"</p><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> powdery snow\"</p><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> rain\"</p><p>\"batiste is a cotton fabric with a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> weave\"</p><p>\"covered with a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> film of dust\"</p></li><li><h5>5. being in good health;</h5><p>\"he's feeling all right again\"</p><p>\"I'm <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b>, how are you?\"</p></li><li><h5>6. thin in thickness or diameter;</h5><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> film of oil\"</p><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> hairs\"</p><p>\"read the <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> print\"</p></li><li><h5>7. characterized by elegance or refinement or accomplishment;</h5><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> wine\"</p><p>\"looking <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> in her Easter suit\"</p><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> gentleman\"</p><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> china and crystal\"</p><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> violinist\"</p><p>\"the <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> hand of a master\"</p></li><li><h5>8. ; free or impurities; having a high or specified degree of purity;</h5><p>\"gold 21 carats <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b>\"</p></li><li><h5>9. (of weather) pleasant; not raining, perhaps with the sun shining;</h5><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> summer evening\"</p></li></ul></div><div class=\"EngMean_eng__Q0uG8\"><h4>Adverb</h4><ul><li><h5>1. sentence-initial expression of agreement</h5></li><li><h5>2. in a delicate manner;</h5><p>\"finely shaped features\"</p><p>\"her <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> drawn body\"</p></li><li><h5>3. in a superior and skilled manner;</h5><p>\"the soldiers were fighting finely\"</p></li></ul></div></div><div class=\"FoldBox_fold__j7cgz\"><h3 class=\"FoldBox_title___fdpp\">英英释义</h3><div class=\"FoldBox_content__HsTfE\"><div class=\"EngMean_eng__Q0uG8\"><h4>Noun</h4><ul><li><h5>1. money extracted as a penalty</h5></li></ul></div><div class=\"EngMean_eng__Q0uG8\"><h4>Verb</h4><ul><li><h5>1. issue a ticket or a fine to as a penalty;</h5><p>\"I was fined for parking on the wrong side of the street\"</p><p>\"Move your car or else you will be ticketed!\"</p></li></ul></div><div class=\"EngMean_eng__Q0uG8\"><h4>Adjective</h4><ul><li><h5>1. superior to the average;</h5><p>\"in <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> spirits\"</p><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> student\"</p><p>\"made good grades\"</p><p>\"morale was good\"</p><p>\"had good weather for the parade\"</p></li><li><h5>2. being satisfactory or in satisfactory condition;</h5><p>\"an all-right movie\"</p><p>\"the passengers were shaken up but are all right\"</p><p>\"is everything all right?\"</p><p>\"everything's <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b>\"</p><p>\"things are okay\"</p><p>\"dinner and the movies had been <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b>\"</p><p>\"another minute I'd have been <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b>\"</p></li><li><h5>3. minutely precise especially in differences in meaning;</h5><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> distinction\"</p></li><li><h5>4. of texture; being small-grained or smooth to the touch or having fine particles;</h5><p>\"wood with a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> grain\"</p><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> powdery snow\"</p><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> rain\"</p><p>\"batiste is a cotton fabric with a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> weave\"</p><p>\"covered with a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> film of dust\"</p></li><li><h5>5. being in good health;</h5><p>\"he's feeling all right again\"</p><p>\"I'm <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b>, how are you?\"</p></li><li><h5>6. thin in thickness or diameter;</h5><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> film of oil\"</p><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> hairs\"</p><p>\"read the <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> print\"</p></li><li><h5>7. characterized by elegance or refinement or accomplishment;</h5><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> wine\"</p><p>\"looking <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> in her Easter suit\"</p><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> gentleman\"</p><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> china and crystal\"</p><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> violinist\"</p><p>\"the <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> hand of a master\"</p></li><li><h5>8. ; free or impurities; having a high or specified degree of purity;</h5><p>\"gold 21 carats <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b>\"</p></li><li><h5>9. (of weather) pleasant; not raining, perhaps with the sun shining;</h5><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">fine</b> summer evening\"</p></li></ul></div><div class=\"EngMean_eng__Q0uG8\"><h4>Adverb</h4><ul><li><h5>1. sentence-initial expression of agreement</h5></li><li><h5>2. in a delicate manner;</h5><p>\"finely shaped features\"</p><p>\"her <b class=\"NormalSentence_cn__gyUtC\"></p><p class=\"NormalSentence_from__cMXrW\">2009年考研真题（英语一）阅读理解 Section Ⅱ</p></div></div></div><div class=\"FoldBox_more__1o39K\"><div class=\"FoldBox_folded__0Cfm6\">收起<!-- -->真题例句<img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\"/></div></div></div></li><div class=\"jsx-1311071109 \"><div html=\"\n                      &lt;div id=&quot;7070364&quot; /&gt;\n                      &lt;script&gt;\n                        (window.slotbydup = window.slotbydup || []).push({\n                          id: &quot;7070364&quot;,\n                          container: &quot;7070364&quot;,\n                          async: true\n                        });\n                      &lt;/script&gt;\"></div></div><li><div class=\"FoldBox_fold__j7cgz\"><h3 class=\"FoldBox_title___fdpp\">英英释义</h3><div class=\"FoldBox_content__HsTfE\"><div class=\"EngMean_eng__Q0uG8\"><h4>Adjective</h4><ul><li><h5>1. not in accordance with the fact or reality or actuality;</h5><p>\"gave <b class=\"highlight\">false</b> testimony under oath\"</p><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">false</b> tales of bravery\"</p></li><li><h5>2. arising from error;</h5><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">false</b> assumption\"</p><p>\"a mistaken view of the situation\"</p></li><li><h5>3. erroneous and usually accidental;</h5><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">false</b> start\"</p><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">false</b> alarm\"</p></li><li><h5>4. deliberately deceptive;</h5><p>\"hollow (or <b class=\"highlight\">false</b>) promises\"</p><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">false</b> pretenses\"</p></li><li><h5>5. inappropriate to reality or facts;</h5><p>\"delusive faith in a wonder drug\"</p><p>\"delusive expectations\"</p><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">false</b> hopes\"</p></li><li><h5>6. not genuine or real; being an imitation of the genuine article;</h5><p>\"it isn't fake anything; it's real synthetic fur\"</p><p>\"faux pearls\"</p><p>\"<b class=\"highlight\">false</b> teeth\"</p><p>\"decorated with imitation palm leaves\"</p><p>\"a purse of simulated alligator hide\"</p></li><li><h5>7. designed to deceive;</h5><p>\"a suitcase with a <b class=\"highlight\">false</b> bottom\"</p></li><li><h5>8. inaccurate in pitch;</h5><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">false</b> (or sour) note\"</p><p>\"her singing was off key\"</p></li><li><h5>9. adopted in order to deceive;</h5><p>\"an assumed name\"</p><p>\"an assumed cheerfulness\"</p><p>\"a fictitious address\"</p><p>\"fictive sympathy\"</p><p>\"a pretended interest\"</p><p>\"a put-on childish voice\"</p><p>\"sham modesty\"</p></li><li><h5>10. (used especially of persons) not dependable in devotion or affection; unfaithful;</h5><p>\"a <b class=\"highlight\">false</b> friend\"</p><p>\"when lovers prove untrue\"</p></li></ul></div><div class=\"EngMean_eng__Q0uG8\"><h4>Adverb</h4><ul><li><h5>1. in a disloyal and faithless manner;</h5><p>\"he behaved treacherously\"</p><p>\"his wife played him <b class=\"highlight\">false</b>\"</p></li></ul></div></div><div class=\"FoldBox_more__1o39K\"><div class=\"FoldBox_folded__0Cfm6\">收起<!-- -->英英释义<img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\"/></div></div></div></li><li><div class=\"FoldBox_fold__j7cgz\"><h3 class=\"FoldBox_title___fdpp\">词根词缀</h3><div class=\"FoldBox_content__HsTfE\"><div class=\"Affix_affix__iiL_9\"><p>词根<!-- -->: <!-- -->fall,fail,fault</p><p>1. =err/deceive,表示&quot;犯错误,欺骗&quot;; 2. = 表示&quot;错,假&quot;</p><ul><li><h4>adj.</h4><div><h5>false<!-- --> <!-- -->错误的,虚伪的,假的,无信义的,伪造的 </h5><p>false错,假→错误的,假的</p></div></li><li><h4>adv.</h4><div><h5>false<!-- --> <!-- -->欺诈地</h5><p>false错,假→错误的,假的</p></div></li><li><h4>n.</h4><div><h5>falsehood<!-- --> <!-- -->错误;撒谎</h5><p>false犯错误,欺骗+hood表名词→n.错误;撒谎</p></div></li><li><h4>v.</h4><div><h5>falsify<!-- --> <!-- -->窜改,说谎</h5><p>fals犯错误,欺骗+ify表动词→弄错→窜改</p></div></li></ul></div></div></div></li><li><div class=\"FoldBox_fold__j7cgz\"><h3 class=\"FoldBox_title___fdpp\">词组搭配</h3><div class=\"FoldBox_content__HsTfE\"><div class=\"Phrase_phrase__W3z3F\"><h5>false position</h5><p>a situation in which one is compelled to act in a manner inconsistent with one&#x27;s true nature or principles</p><p>迫不得已的处境</p></div><div class=\"Phrase_phrase__W3z3F\"><h5>play someone false</h5><p>deceive or cheat someone</p><p>欺骗某人</p></div></div><div class=\"FoldBox_more__1o39K\"><div class=\"FoldBox_folded__0Cfm6\">收起<!-- -->词组搭配<img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\"/></div></div></div></li><li><div class=\"FoldBox_fold__j7cgz\"><h3 class=\"FoldBox_title___fdpp\">同义词辨析</h3><div class=\"FoldBox_content__HsTfE\"><div class=\"SameAnalysis_sameAnalysis__fkwr8\"><h5>artificial, false, synthetic, man-made</h5><p>这些形容词均有&quot;人造的，非自然的&quot;之意。</p><ul><li><h5><span class=\"jsx-1885187966\" href=\"/word?w=artificial\">artificial</span>：指模仿天然材料由人工制造的东西，侧重真伪对比。</h5></li><li><h5><span class=\"jsx-1885187966\" href=\"/word?w=false\">false</span>：指因缺失而补上的替代物，有时也指伪装的。</h5></li><li><h5>synthetic与artificial近义，但前者强调通过化学作用或化学处理把几种物质复制成与原材料截然不同的新产品。</h5></li><li><h5><span class=\"jsx-1885187966\" href=\"/word?w=man-made\">man-made</span>：指完全用人工制造，不含仿造和真伪对比的意味。</h5></li></ul></div><div class=\"SameAnalysis_sameAnalysis__fkwr8\"><h5>fake, false</h5><p>这两个形容词都含有&quot;假的&quot;之意。</p><ul><li><h5><span class=\"jsx-1885187966\" href=\"/word?w=fake\">fake</span>： 指某物不是真的。</h5></li><li><h5><span class=\"jsx-1885187966\" href=\"/word?w=false\">false</span>： 指说明某物与真的相像，强调看上去像真的，不一定用作冒充、谎骗。</h5></li></ul></div></div></div></li><li><div class=\"FoldBox_fold__j7cgz\"><h3 class=\"FoldBox_title___fdpp\">同义词</h3><div class=\"FoldBox_content__HsTfE\"><div class=\"Synonym_synonym__Vv9AM\"><div class=\"Synonym_mean__Xl3X8\"><i>adj.</i><span>不忠的;欺诈的</span><p><span class=\"jsx-1885187966\" href=\"/word?w=two-faced\">two-faced</span><span class=\"jsx-1885187966\" href=\"/word?w=deceitful\">deceitful</span><span class=\"jsx-1885187966\" href=\"/word?w=disloyal\">disloyal</span></p></div><div class=\"Synonym_mean__Xl3X8\"><i>adj.</i><span>假的;伪造的</span><p><span class=\"jsx-1885187966\" href=\"/word?w=counterfeit\">counterfeit</span><span class=\"jsx-1885187966\" href=\"/word?w=artificial\">artificial</span><span class=\"jsx-1885187966\" href=\"/word?w=fake\">fake</span><span
